{
  "texts": [
    "Large language models (LLMs) are artificial intelligence systems trained on large amounts of text data that learn complex language patterns and syntactical relationships to both interpret passages and generate text output 1, 2 LLMs have received widespread attention for their human-like performance on a wide variety of text-generating tasks.",
    "Within medicine, initial efforts have demonstrated that LLMs can write clinical notes 3, pass standardized medical exams 4, and draft responses to patient questions 5, 6.",
    "In order to integrate LLMs more directly into clinical care, it is imperative to better understand their clinical reasoning capabilities.",
    "Clinical reasoning is a set of problem-solving processes specifically designed for diagnosis and management of a patient's medical condition.",
    "Commonly used diagnostic techniques include differential diagnosis formation, intuitive reasoning, analytical reasoning, and Bayesian inference."
  ]
}